article.headline: Radford 60, Liberty 50
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Whit Holcomb-Faye scored 19 points and Chris Oliver grabbed 15 rebounds Saturday night as Radford defeated Liberty 60-50. Liberty missed 27 of its 32 field goal attempts in the first half, allowing Radford (8-6, 1-1 Big South) to take a 23-15 halftime lead. The Flames (4-9, 1-1), who managed just one basket over the last 13 minutes of the half, fared better in the second half but still shot just 29 percent for the game to 38 percent for Radford. Liberty went on a 9-1 run to tie the game at 35 on a pair of free throws by Larry Blair with 11:01 left, but the Highlanders scored six unanswered points for a 41-35 lead. The Flames pulled within one, 48-47, on a 3-pointer by Anthony Smith with 2:47 left, but Holcomb-Faye converted a four-point play to help the Highlanders pull away. Oliver added 14 points and Andre Bynum 13 for Radford. Blair led the Flames with 17 points but was only 5-of-21 from the field. Smith added 11 points.
